head.title: Porta Linguarum, Trilinguis Reserata & Aperta: Seminarium Linguarum & Scientiarum omnium

docTitle.titlePart: Porta Linguarum, Trilinguis Reserata & Aperta: Seminarium Linguarum & Scientiarum omnium

Hoc est, compendiaria Latinam, Anglicam, Gallicam (& quamvis aliam) linguam unà cum artium & scientiarum fundamentis sesquianni spatio ad summum docendi & perdiscendi methodus, sub titulis 100. periodis 1058. comprehensa. Latinè primùm. Nunc verô gratitudinis ergò, in Illustrissimi Principis Caroli, Britaannicaeque Gallicae & Hybernicae pubis gratiam, Latinè, Anglicè, & Gallicè in lucem eruta

titlePage.docAuthor: Opera studio & elucubratione I. A. Comenius. Aestimat ut sapiens pretio non pondere gemmas, utilitate probat sic quoque mentis opus
titlePage.docImprint: LONDINI, Excudebat Edvardus Griffin, Sumptibus Geo. Hutton, in Turnestyle. 1640

docTitle.titlePart: The Gate Of Tongues unlocked and opened. Or Else, A Seminary or Seed-plot of all Tongues and Sciences.

That is, A short way of teaching and thorowly learning within a yeare and a halfe, at the farthest, the Latine, English, French, and any other tongue with the ground and foundation of Arts and Sciences, comprized, under an hundred Titles, and 1058 Periods. In Latine first. And now as a token of thankfulnesse brought to light, in Latine English, and French, in the behalfe of the most Illustrious Prince Charles, and of Brittish, French, and Irish youth.

titlePage.docAuthor: By the labour and indnstry [!] of I. A. Comenius.
titlePage.docImprint: London Printed by Edward Griffin for Georgr Hutton, dwelling at the Swan within Turnestyle in Holborne 1640
